  }, "Why? What were your expectations? Has YugabyteDB delivered on them?"))), mdx("p", null, "We have finished test runs of a major application against YugabyteDB and are evaluating different kinds of setup scenarios to run YugabyteDB in production. The application was originally running on PostgreSQL and, during the test, we only had issues around the pessimistic locking being used for concurrency control in some scenarios which YugabyteDB does not yet cater for. Testing through disaster recovery and upgrade scenarios worked perfectly."), mdx("h3", {
